  profileImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 38cd1686daf57e340bac8d6398cabefe, type: 3}
  profileDescription: <b>Neptune, the eighth and farthest planet from the Sun</b>,
    is known for its pale blue color, intense weather systems, and supersonic winds.
    As an ice giant similar to Uranus, Neptune is a cold, remote world with a unique
    atmosphere and dynamic storms.\n\nNamed after the Roman god of the sea, Neptune
    remains a mysterious and intriguing planet at the outer edge of our Solar System.
  stats:
  - label: Mass
    value: <b>1.02 x 10<sup>26</sup>kg</b>
  - label: Diameter
    value: <b>49,528 km</b>
  - label: Distance to Sun
    value: <b>4,515 million km</b>
  - label: Orbital Period
    value: <b>164 years</b>
  - label: Length of Day
    value: <b>16.1 hours</b>
  - label: Gravity
    value: <b>11 m/s<sup>2</sup></b>
  - label: Satellite count
    value: 16
  - label: Temperature (mean)
    value: "<b>-200 \xB0C</b>"
  - label: Atmosphere
    value: H2+He
