  profileDescription: <b>Jupiter is the fifth planet from the Sun</b> and the largest
    in the Solar System, so massive that it could fit all the other planets inside
    it with room to spare. Known for its striking cloud bands and the Great Red Spot,
    Jupiter is a gas giant with a powerful magnetic field and a dynamic atmosphere.\n\nNamed
    after the king of the Roman gods, Jupiter has fascinated scientists and astronomers
    for centuries.
  stats:
  - label: Mass
    value: <b>1.90 x 10<sup>27</sup>kg</b>
  - label: Diameter
    value: <b>142,984 km</b>
  - label: Distance to Sun
    value: <b>779 million km</b>
  - label: Orbital Period
    value: <b>11.9 years</b>
  - label: Length of Day
    value: <b>9.9 hours</b>
  - label: Gravity
    value: <b>23.10 m/s<sup>2</sup></b>
  - label: Satellite count
    value: 95
  - label: Temperature (mean)
    value: "<b>-110 \xB0C</b>"
  - label: Atmosphere
    value: H2+He
  focusDistanceOverride: 0
  minFocusDistanceOverride: 0
  maxFocusDistanceOverride: 30
