  profileDescription: <b>Venus is the second planet from the Sun</b> and often called
    <b>Earth's sister planet</b> due to its similar size and composition. However,
    despite these surface similarities, Venus is an incredibly hostile world with
    crushing atmospheric pressure, scorching temperatures, and clouds of sulfuric
    acid.\n\nThis enigmatic planet has intrigued humans for centuries and remains
    a key focus of space exploration.
